'''''An Evening Without Monty Python''''' is a stage show produced by WestBeth Entertainment and directed by [[Eric Idle]] and BT McNicholl  in celebration of the comedy troupe [[Monty Python]]'s 40th anniversary, featuring sketches and songs from [[Monty Python's Flying Circus|the show]] hand-picked by Idle.

The show debuted at the [[Ricardo Montalbán Theatre]] in [[Los Angeles]] and played from 23 September to 4 October 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.playbill.com/news/article/133516-An_Evening_Without_Monty_Python_Plays_NYC_Beginning_Oct._6 |title=An Evening Without Monty Python Plays NYC, Beginning Oct. 6 |last=Gans |first=Andrew |date=6 October 2009 |work=Playbill |accessdate=1 December 2009 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091009102215/http://www.playbill.com/news/article/133516-An_Evening_Without_Monty_Python_Plays_NYC_Beginning_Oct._6 |archivedate=9 October 2009 }}</ref> It then moved to [[New York City]], where it played at [[The Town Hall]] from 6 to 10 October 2009.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://theater.nytimes.com/2009/10/08/theater/reviews/08python.html?em|title=And Now for Something Just a Little Bit Different |last=Brantley|first=Ben|date=8 October 2009|work=New York Times |accessdate=1 December 2009}}</ref>

