The '''Greek Film Critics Association''' or '''Pan-Hellenic Film Critics Association''' ({{lang-el|Πανελλήνια Ένωση Κριτικών Κινηματογράφου, ΠΕΚΚ}}) was founded in 1976. The first members were the famous Greek film critics such as [[Nino Fenek Mikelidis]], [[Vasilis Rafailidis]], [[Yannis Bakogiannopoulos]] and others. Since 1977, the association belongs to [[International Federation of Film Critics]] (FIPRESCI).<ref>{{cite web|title=Ίδρυση|url=http://www.pekk.gr/index.php/profile/istoriko|publisher=Πανελλήνια Ένωση Κριτικών Κινηματογράφου|accessdate=4 January 2014|language=Greek}}</ref>
Nearly every year, the PEKK gives out awards during [[Thessaloniki International Film Festival]]. The [[Greek Film Critics Association Awards]] is one of the most important awards for the Greek cinema. The PEKK gives also out award during [[Drama Short Film Festival|Short Film Festival]] in [[Drama, Greece|Drama]].
