'''Hans Nilson Langseth''' (July 14, 1846 – November 10, 1927) was a [[Norwegian Americans|Norwegian-American]] who held the record for the world's longest [[beard]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/world-records/longest-beard-male |title=Longest beard - male |work=[[Guinness World Records]] |accessdate=January 20, 2016}}</ref>

Langseth was born in [[Eidsvoll]] and emigrated to the [[United States]] in 1867. He married Anna Berntsen in 1870 and worked as a farmer in [[Elkton Township, Clay County, Minnesota]]. In his later life, he traveled around the United States as part of a [[freak show]] showing off his beard.<ref>{{cite book |last=Parker |first=Mike |author-link=Mike Parker (writer) |year=1983 |title=The World's Most Fantastic Freaks |location=London |publisher=[[Octopus Publishing Group]] |page=96 |url=https://books.google.es/books?id=lddNAAAAYAAJ}}</ref>

Langseth died aged 81 in [[Wyndmere, North Dakota]] and is buried in Elk Creek Church Cemetery in [[Kensett, Iowa]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Longest Whiskers |url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/4092909/hans_langseth_18461927/ |newspaper=The Greene Recorder |date=November 23, 1927 |page=7 |via=[[Newspapers.com]] |accessdate=January 21, 2016}} {{Open access}}</ref> When he died, his beard measured {{convert|5.33|m|sp=us}}.<ref>{{cite newspaper |url=http://www.dagbladet.no/magasinet/2003/11/12/383312.html |last=Glendrange |first=Sølvi |date=November 12, 2003 |title=Rekord for rekordbok |newspaper=[[Dagbladet]] |publisher=Labrador CMS |language=no}}</ref> It was donated to the Department of Anthropology at the [[Smithsonian Institution]] in 1967.<ref>{{cite book |editor-last=Hunt |editor-first=David R. |editor-link=David R. Hunt |date=May 9, 2008 |chapter=History and Collections of the Division of Physical Anthropology |first=Michael W. |last=Warren |first2=Heather A. |last2=Walsh-Haney |first3=Laurel |last3=Freas |title=The Forensic Anthropology Laboratory |location=Boca Raton, Florida |publisher=[[CRC Press]] |page=155 |url=https://books.google.es/books?id=Vv77SrfNjFMC&pg=PA155}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/magazine-35350886 |title=Are beards good for your health? |newspaper=[[BBC News]] |access-date=January 20, 2016 |date=January 20, 2016}}</ref>

