'''''Snap Judgment''''' is a weekly storytelling radio series and [[podcast]], distributed by the [[WNYC Studios]], and hosted by [[Glynn Washington]]. Each episode is made up of narrative pieces on a common theme. The program first aired in July 2010.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/magazine/archive/2013/07/nprs-great-black-hope/309394/|title=NPR’s Great Black Hope|last=Oppenheimer|first=Mark|website=The Atlantic|language=en-US|access-date=2016-04-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://snapjudgment.org/snap-proudly-annoucnces-new-partnership-wnyc|title=Snap Proudly Announces New Partnership With WNYC! {{!}} Snap Judgment|website=snapjudgment.org|access-date=2016-04-13}}</ref>
